t%20around%204%20p.m.%2C%20there%20was%20a%20knock%20at%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChloe%2C%20thinking%20it%20was%20someone%20else%2C%20opened%20it.%20It%20was%20Young.%20Chloe%20recognized%20him%20from%20the%20Doordash%20delivery.%20He%20asked%20a%20few%20questions%20about%20her%20neighbor%20and%20then%20returned%20to%20his%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20moments%20later%2C%20there%20was%20another%20knock%20at%20the%20door.%20It%20was%20Young%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChloe%2C%20who%20was%20home%20alone%2C%20was%20unnerved.%20She%20opened%20her%20door%20just%20a%20crack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20%E2%80%94%20according%20to%20an%20account%20laid%20out%20in%20criminal%20charging%20documents%2C%20a%20civil%20lawsuit%2C%20and%20interviews%20with%20Chloe%20and%20her%20attorney%20%E2%80%94%20Young%20forced%20his%20way%20inside%2C%20stripped%20off%20his%20pants%2C%20exposed%20himself%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20rape%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20process%2C%20she%20said%2C%20he%20beat%20her%2C%20broke%20her%20nose%2C%20strangled%20her%2C%20and%20bit%20off%20four%20of%20her%20fingertips%20%E2%80%94%20two%20on%20each%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20bit%20my%20fingertips.%20They%20were%20cut%20open%20pretty%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20Chloe%20told%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20bunch%20of%20scrapes%20and%20bruises%20everywhere.%20My%20nose%20was%20fractured.%20I%20had%20a%20bunch%20of%20scratch%20marks%20on%20my%20neck.%20My%20face%20was%20all%20bruised%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20later%20noted%20the%20dried%20blood%20on%20her%20fingers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20had%20a%20history%20of%20violence.%20In%202016%2C%20according%20to%20court%20records%20reviewed%20by%20Insider%2C%20Young%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20charges%20of%20aggravated%20assault%2C%20hit-and-run%2C%20and%20driving%20without%20a%20proper%20license%20after%20he%20ran%20over%20a%20woman%20with%20a%20car%20following%20a%20verbal%20dispute.%20He%20served%20three%20years%20in%20prison%20and%20was%20out%20on%20parole%20while%20working%20for%20Doordash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20grand%20jury%20in%20Coffee%20County%2C%20Georgia%2C%20where%20Chloe%20lives%2C%20brought%20a%20five-count%20indictment%20against%20Young%20over%20the%20incident%20at%20her%20apartment%2C%20charging%20him%20with%20attempted%20rape%20and%20attempted%20murder.%20Chloe's%20last%20name%20is%20known%20to%20Insider%20but%20is%20being%20withheld%20from%20publication%20because%20she%20is%20a%20victim%20of%20sexual%20assault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20judge%20remanded%20Young%20to%20prison%20and%20ordered%20him%20to%20serve%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20sentence%20behind%20bars.%20An%20attorney%20for%20Young%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%2C%20but%20court%20records%20show%20he%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%20the%20new%20set%20of%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDoordash%20says%20it's%20not%20their%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20civil%20lawsuit%20filed%20against%20Doordash%20in%20November%2C%20Chloe%20is%20seeking%20to%20hold%20the%20company%20to%20account%20for%20what%20she%20experienced.%20She%20said%20she%20doesn't%20use%20the%20app%20anymore%2C%20nor%20other%20apps%20that%20use%20third%20parties%20for%20deliveries%2C%20like%20Seamless%20or%20Postmates.%20She%20stays%20away%20from%20other%20%26quot%3Bgig%20economy%26quot%3B%20apps%20like%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20as%20well%2C%20considering%20them%20an%20even%20greater%20safety%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20really%20just%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20doesn't%20happen%20to%20anyone%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Chloe%20said.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20thinks%20that%20it%20can't%20happen%20to%20them%2C%20but%20it%20can.%20And%20I%20feel%20like%20Doordash%20needs%20to%20be%20held%20accountable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChloe%20is%20accusing%20Doordash%20of%20negligence%2C%20alleging%20the%20delivery%20company%20failed%20to%20conduct%20an%20adequate%20background%20check%20on%20Young.%20Doordash%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says%2C%20should%20have%20never%20hired%20Young%20as%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3BDasher%26quot%3B%20or%20given%20him%20access%20to%20her%20home%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Kendall%20Shortway%2C%20a%20lawyer%20representing%20Chloe%2C%20Doordash%20outsources%20many%20background%20checks%20to%20another%20tech%20company%2C%20Checkr.%20Shortway%20intends%20to%20add%20Checkr%20as%20a%20defendant%20in%20the%20case%2C%20she%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetween%20the%20two%20of%20them%2C%20somebody%20dropped%20the%20ball%2C%26quot%3B%20Shortway%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Morgan%20%26amp%3B%20Morgan%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20a%20violent%20felon%20shouldn't%20have%20access%20to%20someone's%20personal%20home%20address.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20that%20use%20Checkr%20tell%20it%20the%20type%20of%20information%20they%20want%20in%20a%20background%20check.%20Shortway%20told%20Insider%20that%20it%20isn't%20yet%20clear%20whether%20Doordash%20didn't%20ask%20whether%20Young%20had%20a%20felony%20conviction%20before%20taking%20him%20on%20as%20a%20deliveryperson%2C%20if%20Checkr%20failed%20to%20discover%20it%2C%20or%20if%20either%20of%20them%20knew%20but%20didn't%20act%20on%20it.%20On%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcheckr.com%2Four-technology%2Fai-powered%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eits%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Checkr%20says%20it%20uses%20artificial%20intelligence%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Befficient%26quot%3B%20way%20to%20conduct%20background%20checks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20what%20DoorDash's%20policy%20is%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20hiring%20drivers%20with%20criminal%20backgrounds.%20Its%20competitor%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fsafety%2F%3Fuclick_id%3Df8bdc5c0-a1f2-4154-b901-cc6e77155cba%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20on%20its%20website%20that%20it%20screens%20applicants%20for%20%26quot%3Bimpaired%20driving%20and%20violent%20offenses%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20Uber%20also%20signed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fcommunity%2Feconomic-opportunities%2Ffresh-chances%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20White%20House's%20%26quot%3BFair%20Chance%20Business%20Pledge%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016%2C%20promising%20not%20to%20discriminate%20against%20job%20applicants%20with%20criminal%20records.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhelp.lyft.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Fall%2Farticles%2F115012925687-Driver-requirements%23bgc%5C%22%3ELyft%3C%2Fa%3E%20explicitly%20warns%20that%20drivers%20could%20be%20ineligible%20for%20%26quot%3Ba%20disqualifying%20violent%20crime%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20aggravated%20assault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20Checkr%20did%20a%20background%20check%2C%20but%20we%20don't%20know%20if%20Doordash%20just%20asked%2C%20'OK%2C%20does%20he%20have%20a%20valid%20driver's%20license%3F'%26quot%3B%20Shortway%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20court%20filing%2C%20Doordash%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bwas%20not%20negligent%20in%20any%20manner%20whatsoever%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20Chloe's%20injuries%20%26quot%3Bwere%20due%20to%20circumstances%20outside%20this%20Defendant's%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoordash%20couldn't%20be%20blamed%20for%20any%20alleged%20misconduct%2C%20the%20company%20argued%20in%20the%20filing%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20because%20of%20Young's%20%26quot%3Bstatus%20as%20an%20independent%20contractor%2C%20and%20not%20as%20an%20employee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20basically%20saying%2C%20'He's%20an%20independent%20contractor%20and%20it's%20not%20our%20fault%2C'%26quot%3B%20Shortway%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20Doordash%20asked%20Insider%20for%20a%20response%20deadline%20for%20this%20story%20and%20then%20didn't%20respond%20to%20subsequent%20requests%20for%20comment%20over%20several%20days.%20Checkr%20didn't%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20ultimately%20left%20Chloe's%20home%20after%20she%20told%20him%20she%20heard%20her%20boyfriend's%20car%20outside.%20She's%20still%20not%20sure%20how%20long%20he%20was%20in%20her%20house.%20Neighbors%20noted%20his%20car%20in%20the%20driveway%20at%204%20p.m.%2C%20and%20police%20weren't%20dispatched%20until%207%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20is%20trapped%20in%20the%20house%20with%20him%2C%20and%20all%20of%20this%20is%20going%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Shortway%20said.%20%26quot%3BHer%20fingertips%20were%20actually%20bitten%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-rejects-responsibility-alleged-dasher-rape-murder-attempt-fingertips-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691327701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cd471ef5d4870019e1ff4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-rejects-responsibility-alleged-dasher-rape-murder-attempt-fingertips-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20woman%20who%20ordered%20food%20from%20Doordash%20says%20the%20driver%20returned%20to%20her%20house%20days%20later%2C%20tried%20to%20rape%20her%2C%20and%20bit%20off%20her%20fingertips.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jshamsian%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Shamsian)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A57%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-rejects-responsibility-alleged-dasher-rape-murder-attempt-fingertips-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pakistan%20passenger%20train%20derails%20killing%2030%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691327583000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FB867%2Fproduction%2F_130670274_de27.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66421481%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Several%20coaches