%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20NASA%20isn't%20putting%20all%20its%20stock%20in%20SpaceX.%20Blue%20Origin%20recently%20won%20a%20%243.4%20billion%20contract%20for%20NASA's%20Artemis%20V%20human%20lunar%20launcher%2C%20a%20win%20for%20a%20company%20that%20had%20lost%20its%20previous%20bids%20to%20SpaceX.%20The%20contract%20should%20boost%20the%20development%20of%20the%20company's%20own%20mega-rocket%2C%20New%20Glenn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20NASA's%20SLS%20spacecraft%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20built%20and%20developed%20in-house%2C%20a%20relic%20of%20NASA's%20old%20approach%20to%20rocket%20development%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20big%20money%20for%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%20was%20awarded%20a%20%242.7%20billion%20contract%20and%20a%20%241.9%20billion%20extension%20to%20deliver%20six%20Orion%20spacecraft%20for%20the%20Artemis%20missions%20III%20to%20VIII.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20market%20may%20not%20be%20self-sustaining%20before%20mid-2030%2C%20but%20that%20may%20not%20matter%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20NASA%20remains%20the%20most%20prominent%20client%20in%20the%20lunar%20market.%20If%20the%20US%20government%20decided%20tomorrow%20to%20pull%20its%20backing%20from%20private%20investment%2C%20it's%20possible%20the%20market%20wouldn't%20survive%20off%20its%20own%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20investment%20in%20extraplanetary%20exploration%20and%20exploitation%20has%20only%20just%20started%20to%20trickle%20in%2C%20which%20is%20encouraging%2C%20Kawade%20said.%20For%20instance%2C%20AstroForge%2C%20an%20asteroid-mining%20startup%20in%20California%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2022%2F05%2F26%2Fastroforge-raises-13m-seed-round-for-asteroid-mining-ambitions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20raised%20%2413%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20private%20capital%20for%20two%20upcoming%20missions.%20Lunar%20Outpost%2C%20a%20space-tech%20firm%20from%20Colorado%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesswire.com%2Fnews%2Fhome%2F20220524005399%2Fen%2FLunar-Outpost-Announces-12-Million-Seed-Investment-to-Scale-Mobility-Technology-Enabling-Commercial-Lunar-Advancement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraised%20%2412%20million%20in%20seed%20investment%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20develop%20lunar%20rovers%20and%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20if%20the%20market%20is%20to%20be%20self-sustaining%2C%20companies%20will%20need%20to%20find%20other%20clients%20to%20buy%20what%20they%20are%20selling%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20clear%20whether%20anyone%20has%20cracked%20this%20business%20model%2C%20Rosseau%20said.%20Still%2C%20Rosseau%20anticipates%2C%20this%20flash%20point%20could%20be%20coming%20in%20the%20mid-2030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20what%20really%20gets%20investors%20and%20businesses%20excited%20is%20seeing%20these%20huge%20tailwinds%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20lunar%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20the%20lunar%20market%20can%20survive%20without%20NASA%20might%20be%20missing%20the%20point%20anyway%2C%20Kawade%20said.%20On%20the%20way%20to%20the%20moon%2C%20companies%20are%20likely%20to%20discover%20technologies%20that%20can%20have%20lucrative%20applications%20here%20on%20Earth%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20NASA's%20lead%2C%20others%20have%20also%20started%C2%A0looping%C2%A0in%20the%20private%20sector%20to%20their%20space%20exploration%20programs%2C%20including%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pwc.com.au%2Findustry%2Fspace-industry%2Flunar-market-assessment-2021.pdf%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pwc.com.au%2Findustry%2Fspace-industry%2Flunar-market-assessment-2021.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EJapan%2C%20China%2C%20and%20Russia%3C%2Fa%3E's%20space%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWelcome%20to%20the%20space%20race%20of%20the%202020s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoney%20isn't%20the%20only%20drive%20pushing%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20to%20bring%20businesses%20to%20the%20moon.%20There%20are%20strong%20political%20incentives%20to%20get%20there%20before%20China%2C%20Rosseau%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20fact%3A%20We're%20in%20a%20space%20race%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA's%20current%20administrator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-bill-nelson-warns-china-claim-moon-territory-lunar-resources-2023-1%5C%22%3EBill%20Nelson%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Politico%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20true%20that%20we%20better%20watch%20out%20that%20they%20don't%20get%20to%20a%20place%20on%20the%20moon%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20scientific%20research%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20is%20not%20beyond%20the%20realm%20of%20possibility%20that%20they%20say%2C%20'Keep%20out%2C%20we're%20here%2C%20this%20is%20our%20territory.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2024%20space-faring%20nations%20have%20signed%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fspecials%2Fartemis-accords%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS's%20Artemis%20Accords%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20set%20of%20rules%20drawn%20up%20by%20NASA%20for%20international%20cooperation%20on%20the%20moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20was%20not%20one%20of%20them.%C2%A0The%20nation%20has%20set%20its%20own%20independent%20path%20to%20the%20moon%2C%20for%20which%20it%20is%20seeking%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gisreportsonline.com%2Fr%2Fchina-space-latin%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecloser%20relations%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20space%20agencies%20in%20Russia%2C%20Latin%20America%2C%20and%20Central%20Asia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20still%20dominates%20space.%20It%20has%20more%20satellites%20in%20orbit%20%E2%80%94%203%2C433%20US%20satellites%20in%20orbit%20versus%20541%20for%20China%20%E2%80%94%20and%20has%20more%20budget%20%E2%80%94%20about%20%2460%20billion%20in%202021%20versus%20about%20%2416%20billion%20for%20China%2C%20Svetla%20Ben-Itzhak%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20Air%20University%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20recently%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fis-the-us-in-a-space-race-against-china-203473%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20told%20%3C%2Fa%3EThe%20Conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20China%20is%20moving%20toward%20the%20moon%20on%20a%20competitive%20timeline.%20It%20attempted%2055%20launches%20in%202021%2C%20four%20more%20than%20the%20US%2C%20per%20Ben-Itzhak.%20It%20was%20also%20the%20first%20nation%20to%20put%20a%20spacecraft%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffar-side-of-the-moon-china-rover-explores-tracks-2019-1%5C%22%3Efar%20side%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20moon%20in%202019%20and%20has%20launched%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-to-launch-first-people-to-new-space-station-2021-6%5C%22%3Eown%20crewed%20space%20station%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20orbit%2C%20just%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-pull-iss-2024-build-own-space-station-roscosmos-putin-2022-7%5C%22%3EInternational%20Space%20Station%20is%20nearing%20the%20end%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20US%20and%20China%20are%20signatories%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftreaties.unoda.org%2Fa%2Fouter_space%2Fchina%2FACC%2Fwashington%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Republic%2520of%2520China%2520signed%2Csole%2520legal%2520government%2520of%2520China%2520.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOuter%20Space%20Treaty%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20means%20they've%20agreed%20that%20no%20country%20can%20militarize%20or%20claim%20the%20moon.%20But%20there%20is%20still%20considerable%20%26quot%3Bfirst-mover%20advantage%26quot%3B%20to%20whichever%20business%20gets%20there%20first%2C%20said%20Rousseau%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20issue%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20interoperability%20between%20infrastructures.%20While%20NASA%20has%20been%20working%20with%20collaborators%20to%20develop%20a%20language%20that%20could%20be%20used%20across%20all%20lunar%20devices%2C%20China%20has%20not%20been%20participating.%20If%20it%20gets%20there%20first%2C%20it%20could%20set%20a%20different%20standard%2C%20foiling%20the%20US%20allies'%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20real%20incentive%20for%20liberal%20democracies%20to%20get%20there%20%E2%80%94%20whoever%20gets%20there%20writes%20the%20rules%20essentially%2C%26quot%3B%20Rousseau%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-helping-private-companies-build-business-moon-make-lunar-billions-2023-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691325849000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F649da68ab923dd0019c40278%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-helping-private-companies-build-business-moon-make-lunar-billions-2023-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20NASA%20aims%20to%20stay%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20private%20firms%20are%20racing%20to%20be%20the%20first%20to%20go%20where%20no%20company%20has%20gone%20before.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mguenot%40businessinsider.com%20(Marianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A55%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-helping-private-companies-build-business-moon-make-lunar-billions-2023-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%5C%22Middle%20Order%20Crumbled%20Without%20Virat%2C%20Rohit%5C%22%3A%20Ex-Ind%20Star%20Warns%20Youngsters%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20recently-concluded%20India%20vs%20West%20Indies%20three-match%20ODI%20series%20was%20a%20good%20test%20for%20the%20former%20team%20that%20continues%20to%20prepare