e%20of%20the%20War%20on%20the%20Rocks%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwarontherocks.com%2F2023%2F07%2Fukraine-struggles-to-scale-offensive-combat-operations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we're%20seeing%20in%20the%20south%2C%20they've%20developed%20ways%20of%20dealing%20%5Bwith%5D%20and%20mitigating%20some%20of%20those%20kinds%20of%20weaknesses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20less%20important%20sectors%20are%20defended%20by%20newly%20conscripted%20troops%20with%20poor%20training%20and%20equipment%20and%20by%20the%20notorious%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Frussia-storm-z-convict-units-mistreatment-crimea-defense-ministry-1814363%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStorm%20Z%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20convicts%20who%20have%20agreed%20to%20fight%20in%20Ukraine%20in%20exchange%20for%20being%20released%20from%20prison.%20That%20frees%20up%20better-quality%20troops%2C%20including%20some%20regular%20motorized%20rifle%20units%20as%20well%20as%20special%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222386%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20Naval%20Infantry%20Marines%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F54dbbec2ecad04e81aa75725%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221592%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20marines%20during%20combined%20exercises%20with%20Ukraine's%20military%20near%20Sevastopol%20in%20May%202011.%3Cp%3EStringer%20Russia%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNaval%20infantry%2C%20the%20more%20elite%20units%2C%20are%20being%20used%20either%20to%20counterattack%20or%20they're%20being%20used%20at%20strong%20points%2C%20the%20most%20important%20parts%20of%20the%20frontline%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20misused%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-galeotti-putins-wars-book-excerpt-russia-spetsnaz-forces-2023-4%5C%22%3Eits%20Spetsnaz%20commandos%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20assault%20infantry%20during%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20invasion%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-military-wasted-special-operations-units-in-ukraine-invasion-2023-5%5C%22%3Eto%20compensate%20for%20the%20weaknesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20line%20infantry%2C%20but%20Spetsnaz%20armed%20with%20anti-tank%20missiles%20are%20now%20being%20reserved%20to%20lead%20counterattacks%2C%20Lee%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20Ukraine%20commits%20to%20an%20advance%20in%20one%20direction%2C%20Russia%20can%20then%20move%20its%20elite%20units%20to%20reinforce%20its%20weaker%20units.%20Psychologically%20it%20means%20that%20it's%20more%20likely%20the%20poor%20units%20will%20actually%20fight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20Army%20has%20so%20far%20followed%20its%20own%20doctrine%20for%20defense.%20Disposable%20troops%2C%20heavily%20entrenched%20and%20supported%20by%20dense%20minefields%20and%20plentiful%20artillery%20%E2%80%94%20though%20Russian%20artillery%20ammo%20supplies%20are%20a%20growing%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20are%20put%20on%20the%20front%20line%20while%20elite%20troops%20are%20held%20for%20counterattacks%20to%20dislodge%20Ukrainian%20assault%20units%20before%20they%20can%20consolidate%20their%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20many%20cases%20when%20they%20counterattack%2C%20this%20is%20fundamentally%20a%20battle%20of%20tree%20lines%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said%20of%20Ukraine's%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Ukrainian%20forces%20advance%20and%20take%20a%20tree%20line%2C%20Russian%20armor%20moves%20out%20and%20begins%20to%20engage%20that%20entire%20tree%20line%20at%20the%20range%20of%20a%20couple%20of%20kilometers.%20The%20Ukrainian%20forces%20that%20took%20that%20tree%20line%2C%20if%20they%20don't%20have%20effective%20anti-tank%20guided%20missiles%20with%20them%20that%20don't%20have%20the%20range%20to%20reach%20Russian%20armor%2C%20and%20since%20much%20of%20the%20f