ct%20the%20growing%20demand%20for%20US%20workers%20in%20the%20semiconductor%20industry.%20Last%20summer%2C%20President%20Biden%20signed%20into%20law%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchips-act-bill-to-boost-us-chipmaking-competition-with-china-2022-7%5C%22%3EChips%20and%20Science%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20included%20over%20%2452%20billion%20in%20semiconductor%20subsidies%20to%20bolster%20supply%20chains%20and%20reduce%20the%20US's%20dependence%20on%20China%20and%20Taiwan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legislation%20has%20helped%20spur%20the%20building%20of%20US%20factories%20that%20produce%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-tim-cook-america-us-made-chips-first-time-decade-2022-12%5C%22%3Esemiconductor%20chips%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20power%20everything%20from%20iPhones%20to%20cars%20to%20washing%20machines.%20But%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20center%20of%20the%20industry%20is%20Arizona%2C%20the%20nation's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-tsmc-chipmaker-investing-billions-us-cost-more-make-chips-2022-12%5C%22%3Eleader%20in%20semiconductor%20investment%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20home%20to%20two%20of%20the%20three%20largest%20semiconductor%20manufacturers%20in%20the%20world%3A%20Intel%20and%20TSMC.%20Since%20February%20of%202021%2C%2024%20semiconductor-related%20companies%20have%20announced%20plans%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2Flocal%2Fphoenix%2F2023%2F03%2F02%2Fphoenix-semiconductor-chips-tsmc-intel-asm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpand%20or%20relocate%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20operations%20in%20Arizona%2C%20per%20Axios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrograms%20like%20the%20one%20enrolled%20in%20by%20Strothers%20are%20designed%20to%20address%20a%20shortage%20of%20skilled%20workers.%20Deloitte%20estimates%20that%20the%20industry%20could%20face%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.deloitte.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2FDeloitte%2Fus%2FDocuments%2Ftechnology-media-telecommunications%2Fus-tmt-global-semiconductor-shortage-pov-v3.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshortfall%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2070%2C000%20to%2090%2C000%20workers%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that's%20already%20caused%20the%20opening%20of%20a%20TSMC%20facility%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F07%2F21%2Ftech%2Ftsmc-arizona-production-delay%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelayed%20until%202025%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cesar%20Becerra%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ca75f095fe1f0019def877%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Quick%20Start%20program%20class%3Cp%3ECesar%20Becerra%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20cue%2C%20community%20colleges%20and%20universities%20across%20the%20country%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechmonitor.ai%2Ftechnology%2Fsilicon%2Fcan-universities-fix-the-semiconductor-talent-shortage%5C%22%3Epartnering%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20chipmakers%20like%20Intel%2C%20TSMC%2C%20Micron%2C%20and%20GlobalFoundries%20to%20try%20and%20close%20the%20gap.%20The%20Quick%20Start%20program's%20website%20says%20that%20semiconductor%20companies%20will%20hire%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finfo.maricopacorporate.com%2Fsemiconductor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%2020%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20workers%20in%20Arizona%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20become%20a%20semiconductor%20technician%20in%2010%20days%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20a%20%2415%20registration%20fee%2C%20the%20tuition%20for%20the%2010-day%20MCCC%20course%20is%20%24291.%20But%20the%20tuition%20isn't%20paid%20up%20front%2C%20and%20any%20Arizona%20resident%20who%20successfully%20passes%20the%20course%20has%20their%20tuition%20fully%20covered%20by%20grant%20funding%20%E2%80%94%20non-residents%20are%20partially%20covered.%20Costs%20are%20subject%20to%20changes%20in%20future%20grant%20funding%2C%20an%20MCCC%20representative%20noted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrothers%20said%20that%20most%20of%20the%2015%20to%2020%20students%20in%20her%20class%20%E2%80%94%20which%20consisted%20entirely%20of%20women%20%E2%80%94%20didn't%20have%20any%20tech%20background.%20The%20test%20pilot%20group%20was%20sourced%20by%20Fresh%20Start%20Women's%20Foundation%2C%20a%20Phoenix-based%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreshstartwomen.org%2F%3Fgclid%3DCjwKCAjw_aemBhBLEiwAT98FMkiX1Koenu3CffMTewh80WCjWDjL3MxvTvz0okKWnsuufRCBXE5eMBoCI6sQAvD_BwE%5C%22%3Enonprofit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20MCCC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20June%2C%2066%25%20of%20students%20who%20enrolled%20in%20the%20program%20have%20been%20people%20of%20color%2C%20one-third%20have%20been%20women%2C%20and%20nearly%20half%20have%20been%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2018%20and%2029%2C%20according%20to%20MCCC%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrothers%20said%20the%2010-day%20course%20consisted%20of%20a%20mix%20of%20lecturing%20and%20hands-on%20experience%2C%20and%20that%20all%20of%20her%20instructors%20were%20Intel%20employees%2C%20which%20provided%20valuable%20firsthand%20knowledge%20of%20what%20it's%20like%20to%20work%20in%20the%20semiconductor%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20lectures%2C%20she%20said%20she%20learned%20about%20the%20specific%20role%20semiconductor%20processing%20technicians%20play%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20process.%20During%20the%20hands-on%20portion%2C%20students%20put%20on%20%26quot%3Bbunny%20suits%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20garments%20used%20to%20minimize%20contaminants%20%E2%80%94%20and%20practiced%20performing%20troubleshooting%20on%20a%20variety%20of%20tools%20in%20a%20simulation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.techtarget.com%2Fsearchstorage%2Fdefinition%2Fsemiconductor-fab%3FOffer%3Dabt_pubpro_AI-Insider%5C%22%3Efab%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221796%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lisa%20Strothers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cceb510b651c00193ac8b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221347%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELisa%20Strothers%3Cp%3ELisa%20Strothers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20course%20concluded%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20two%20weeks%20with%20a%20final%20exam%2C%20which%20Strothers%20said%20had%20written%20and%20hands-on%20components.%20She%20passed%20the%20exam%20and%20received%20her%20program%20certificate%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nims-skills.org%2Fsemiconductor-pre-apprentice-credential%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esemiconductor%20pre-apprentice%20credential%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Among%20students%20who%20attempted%20the%20full%20program%2C%2093%25%20of%20them%20earned%20the%20final%20certification%20as%20of%20June%2C%20according%20to%20MCCC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20a%20week%20later%2C%20Strothers%20began%20interviewing%20for%20new%20roles%20%E2%80%94%20the%20interviews%20are%20typically%20set%20up%20at%20job%20fairs%20on%20MCCC's%20campuses.%20She%20ultimately%20landed%20a%20semiconductor%20processing%20technician%20role%20at%20Intel's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.exploreintel.com%2Focotillo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOcotillo%3C%2Fa%3E%20factory%2C%20which%20she%20began%20last%20August%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20just%20four%20months%20after%20she'd%20been%20laid%20off.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20240%20former%20Quick%20Start%20students%20who%20filled%20out%20an%20employment%20outcome%20form%20as%20of%20June%2030th%2C%2075%2C%20or%2031%25%2C%20said%20they%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bhired%20in%20field%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20MCCC.%20The%20others%20were%20either%20still%20looking%20for%20employment%2C%2058%25%2C%20or%20not%20looking%20for%20work%2C%208%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20program's%20strong%20connection%20to%20Intel%2C%20an%20MCCC%20representative%C2%A0told%20Insider%20that%20all%20the%20area's%20semiconductor%20companies%20are%20part%20of%20an%20advisory%20board%20that%20oversees%20the%20program%20and%20that%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20funnel%20students%20to%20all%20of%20these%20employers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%2012-hour%20shifts%20are%20tough%2C%20but%20the%20job%20is%20%26quot%3Bnever%20boring%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStrothers%20said%20there%20are%20pros%20and%20cons%20to%20the%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPros%3A%20She's%20earning%20a%20bit%20more%20than%20she%20did%20at%20her%20previous%20role%20and%20said%20Intel%20has%20a%20solid%20benefits%20program.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrothers%20declined%20to%20provide%20her%20income%20for%20privacy%20reasons%2C%20but%20the%20average%20annual%20income%20of%20Quick%20Start%20graduates%20is%20roughly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6289816%2Fbiden-chips-workforce-training%2F%5C%22%3E%2443%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Fresh%20Start.%20The%20MCCC%20website%20says%20entry-level%20technicians%20earn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finfo.maricopacorporate.com%2Fsemiconductor%5C%22%3E%2420%20to%20%2425%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20hour%20depending%20on%20their%20experience.%20The%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20lists%20the%20median%20annual%20income%20for%20semiconductor%20processing%20technicians%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Foes%2Fcurrent%2Foes519141.htm%5C%22%3Eroughly%20%2445%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22students%20at%20Quick%20Start%20program%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ca5af295fe1f0019dec1d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECesar%20Becerra%3Cp%3ECesar%20Becerra%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20positive%3A%20The%20job%20is%20%26quot%3Bnever%20boring.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20day%20you%20come%20to%20work%2C%20you%20are%20going%20to%20learn%20something%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20like%20that%20this%20job%20keeps%20my%20interest.%20I'm%20constantly%20learning%20and%20I'm%20constantly%20in%20training%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrothers%20described%20her%20position%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bpoint%20of%20contact%26quot%3B%20role%20%E2%80%94%20a%20middle%20person%20between%20the%20techs%20who%20physically%20work%20on%20the%20tools%20and%20the%20engineers%2C%20which%20they%20call%20%26quot%3Btool%20owners.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20most%20days%20consist%20of%20a%20few%20morning%20meetings%2C%20and%20then%20she%20is%20given%20a%20list%20of%20tasks%20that%20are%20typically%20related%20to%20troubleshooting%20or%20maintenance%20on%20a%20tool.%20She%20said%20most%20of%20her%20work%20is%20done%20on%20a%20computer%2C%20but%20that%20some%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bhealth%20checks%26quot%3B%20on%20tools%20are%20more%20hands-on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20she%20really%20likes%20her%20team.%20Even%20though%20she's%20the%20only%20one%20without%20any%20prior%20background%20in%20the%20field%2C%20she%20said%20they%20are%20all%20very%20patient%20and%20help%20her%20learn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20downside%20to%20her%20job%2C%20Strothers%20said%2C%20is%20her%20schedule%2C%20which%20consists%20of%2012-hour%20shifts%20three-to-four%20days%20per%20week%20%E2%80%94%20the%20number%20of%20days%20changes%20each%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20start%20work%20at%205%3A45%20AM%2C%20and%20I%20get%20off%20at%206%3A15%20PM%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20having%20that%20type%20of%20schedule%2C%20and%20obviously%20being%20a%20single%20mom%2C%20that's%20been%20a%20little%20difficult.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrothers%20has%2