2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Oppenheimer%20Did%20Not%20Stop%20at%20Building%20a%20Nuclear%20Bomb.%20He%20Also%20Pushed%20for%20its%20Use%20in%20Japan.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F06114151%2FOppenheimer-Movie-Poster_1658466334143_1658466388193_1658466388193.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EToday%2C%20August%206%2C%20marks%20the%2078th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20destruction%20of%20Hiroshima%20by%20an%20atomic%20bomb%20dropped%20on%20the%20city%20by%20the%20United%20States%20during%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20well-made%20movie.%20It%20portrays%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20personal%20struggles%2C%20and%20draws%20attention%20to%20the%20dangers%20of%20a%20nuclear%20arms%20race.%20However%2C%20the%20movie%20fails%20to%20emphasise%20that%20during%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20Oppenheimer%20did%20not%20restrict%20himself%20to%20the%20problem%20of%20building%20a%20nuclear%20bomb.%20He%20advocated%20for%20its%20use%20in%20Japan%2C%20over%20other%20possible%20options%2C%20and%20played%20a%20role%20in%20planning%20its%20delivery%20so%20that%20it%20would%20take%20as%20many%20lives%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%201945%2C%20just%20days%20after%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20surrender%2C%20a%20committee%20comprising%20a%20number%20of%20scientists%20and%20some%20military%20officials%20convened%20to%20discuss%20possible%20targets%20for%20the%20bomb.%20The%20movie%20alludes%20to%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20with%20this%20process%20but%2C%20contrary%20to%20what%20is%20suggested%20there%2C%20Oppenheimer%20was%20not%20a%20marginal%20participant%3B%20the%20committee%20met%20in%20his%20office%20and%20he%20was%20the%20one%20who%20set%20out%20the%20agenda.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnsarchive2.gwu.edu%2FNSAEBB%2FNSAEBB162%2F6.pdf%5C%22%3Emeeting%E2%80%99s%20summary%3C%2Fa%3E%20reveals%20how%20the%20committee%20calmly%20considered%20the%20most%20effective%20possible%20destruction%20of%20various%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKyoto%20was%20placed%20on%20top%20of%20the%20list%20and%20ranked%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9CAA%20target%E2%80%9D.%20The%20committee%20noted%20that%20it%20had%20%E2%80%9Ca%20population%20of%201%2C000%2C000%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20many%20people%20and%20industries%20are%20now%20being%20moved%20there%20as%20other%20areas%20are%20being%20destroyed%E2%80%9D.%20It%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%9CKyoto%20has%20the%20advantage%20of%20the%20people%20being%20more%20highly%20intelligent%20and%20hence%20better%20able%20to%20appreciate%20the%20significance%20of%20the%20weapon.%E2%80%9D%20Even%20by%20Orientalist%20standards%2C%20this%20argument%20was%20extraordinary%3A%20did%20the%20committee%20seriously%20believe%20that%20those%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20Japan%20were%20too%20dull%20to%20feel%20the%20terror%20of%20a%20nuclear%20bomb%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20movie%20notes%2C%20Kyoto%20was%20spared%20because%20of%20the%20intervention%20of%20the%20US%20secretary%20of%20war%2C%20Henry%20Stimson.%20Next%20on%20the%20target%20committee%E2%80%99s%20list%20was%20Hiroshima%2C%20which%20was%20also%20rated%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9CAA%20target%E2%80%9D.%20The%20committee%20observed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20such%20a%20size%20that%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20city%20could%20be%20extensively%20damaged.%20There%20are%20adjacent%20hills%2C%20which%20are%20likely%20to%20produce%20a%20focusing%20effect%20which%20would%20considerably%20increase%20the%20blast%20damage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20month%20later%2C%20a%20group%20of%20scientists%20led%20by%20James%20Franck%2C%20and%20including%20the%20physicist%20Leo%20Szilard%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsgp.fas.org%2Feprint%2Ffranck.html%5C%22%3Ecompiled%20a%20prescient%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20analysed%20the%20dangers%20of%20an%20arms%20race%2C%20and%20the%20possibility%20of%20an%20international%20agreement%20to%20control%20nuclear%20weapons.%20It%20advised%20the%20US%20government%20not%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbe%20the%20first%20to%20release%20this%20new%20means%20of%20indiscriminate%20destruction%20upon%20mankind%E2%80%9D.%20Instead%20it%20recommended%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnuclear%20bombs%E2%80%A6%5Bbe%5D%E2%80%A6first%20revealed%20to%20the%20world%20by%20a%20demonstration%20in%20an%20appropriately%20selected%20uninhabited%20area%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20few%20days%2C%20the%20scientific%20advisory%20panel%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinterim%20committee%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20the%20apex%20wartime%20body%20on%20nuclear%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20dismissed%20the%20Franck%20report%20stating%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20see%20no%20acceptable%20alternative%20to%20direct%20military%20use%E2%80%9D.%20Oppenheimer%20signed%20the%20memo%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnsarchive2.gwu.edu%2FNSAEBB%2FNSAEBB162%2F19.pdf%5C%22%3Erecommendations%20on%20the%20immediate%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20four-member%20scientific%20panel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESzilard%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fahf%2Fkey-documents%2Fszilard-petition%2F%5C%22%3Edrafted%20a%20petition%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20US%20president.%20The%20petition%20urged%20the%20president%20%E2%80%9Cto%20rule%20that%20the%20United%20States%20shall%20not%20resort%20to%20the%20use%20of%20atomic%20bombs%20in%20this%20war%20unless%20the%20terms%20which%20will%20be%20imposed%20upon%20Japan%20have%20been%20made%20public%20in%20detail%E2%80%9D%20and%20consider%20%E2%80%9Call%20the%20other%20moral%20responsibilities%20which%20are%20involved%E2%80%9D.%20This%20was%20so%20reasonable%20that%20even%20the%20hawkish%20physicist%20Edward%20Teller%20agreed%20with%20it.%20Oppenheimer%20not%20only%20refused%20to%20sign%20the%20petition%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20scene%20in%20the%20movie%20shows%20%E2%80%94%20he%20prevailed%20on%20others%20at%20Los%20Alamos%2C%20including%20Teller%2C%20to%20withhold%20their%20signature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20war%2C%20in%201949%2C%20Oppenheimer%20testified%20before%20the%20House%20Un-American%20Activities%20Committee.%20This%20was%20separate%20from%20his%20later%20hearings%20before%20the%20US%20Atomic%20Energy%20Commission%20(AEC)%20that%20provide%20the%20setting%20for%20the%20movie.%20In%201949%2C%20the%20committee%20was%20deferential%20to%20Oppenheimer%20and%20he%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20freely%20denounced%20a%20number%20of%20his%20associates%2C%20including%20his%20former%20student%20Bernard%20Peters.%20Peters%20was%20eventually%20forced%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20spent%20several%20years%20in%20Mumbai%20at%C2%A0%20the%20Tata%20Institute%20of%20Fundamental%20Research%20before%20moving%20to%20Denmark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOppenheimer%20did%20argue%20for%20a%20more%20rational%20nuclear%20policy%20after%20the%20war.%20His%20perspective%20was%20not%20rooted%20in%20a%20principled%20opposition%20to%20US%20hegemony%20or%20in%20a%20desire%20for%20a%20more%20equitable%20world%20order.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F20030987%5C%22%3EHis%20argument%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20simpler%3A%20%E2%80%9Clooking%20ten%20years%20ahead%2C%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20small%20comfort%20that%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20is%20four%20years%20behind%20us%E2%80%9D%20in%20developing%20an%20atomic%20arsenal.%20%E2%80%9COur%20twenty-thousandth%20bomb%E2%80%A6will%20not%20in%20any%20deep%20strategic%20sense%20offset%20their%20two-thousandth%E2%80%9D.%20Even%20this%20was%20unacceptable%20to%20sections%20of%20the%20US%20establishment%20and%20eventually%20led%20to%20his%20political%20downfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AEC%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20revoke%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20security%20clearance%20in%201954%20meant%20that%20he%20ceased%20to%20be%20a%20formal%20government%20advisor.%20But%20Oppenheimer%20remained%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Institute%20for%20Advanced%20Study%20at%20Princeton%20and%20a%20privileged%20member%20of%20US%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20this%20author%20is%20not%20an%20expert%20on%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20he%20possessed%20a%20complex%20personality.%20Perhaps%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20actions%20should%20be%20viewed%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbanality%20of%20evil%E2%80%9D.%20As%20an%20ambitious%20individual%20seeking%20advancement%20within%20the%20US%20system%2C%20he%20made%20repeated%20compromises%20and%20lost%20sight%20of%20the%20true%20nature%20of%20the%20US%20military%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20reason%2C%20the%20movie%E2%80%99s%20most%20problematic%20aspect%20is%20not%20that%20it%20is%20overly%20sympathetic%20to%20Oppenheimer.%20Rather%2C%20by%C2%A0%20glorifying%20the%20Manhattan%20project%20and%20the%20US%20victory%20in%20the%20technical%20race%20to%20build%20the%20bomb%2C%20it%20obscures%20the%20enormity%20of%20the%20crime%20committed%20by%20the%20Truman%20administration%20when%20it%20bombed%20Hiroshima%20and%20Nagasaki%20in%20August%201945.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bombs%20killed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebulletin.org%2F2020%2F08%2Fcounting-the-dead-at-hiroshima-and-nagasaki%2F%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20thousands%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20people%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20whom%20were%20innocent%20civilians.%20A%20grim%20indicator%20of%20how%20many%20children%20lost%20their%20lives%20is%20that%20when%20scientists%20sought%20to%20estimate%20the%20toll%20of%20the%20bombings%2C%20they%20relied%20on%20school%20records%20to%20calculate%20a%20statistical%20mortality%20rate%20in%20the%20general%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20apologists%20have%20consistently%20sought%20to%20justify%20these%20acts%20by%20arguing%20that%20a%20land%20invasion%20of%20Japan%20might%20have%20been%20even%20more%20brutal.%20Some%20historians%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F01402399908437744%5C%22%3Ehave%20questioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20veracity%20of%20such%20claims.%20But%20this%20is%20a%20false%20dichotomy%20since%20these%20were%20not%20the%20only%20two%20options%20before%20the%20US%20government.%20And%20accepting%20these%20terms%20of%20discourse%20leads%20to%20a%20blind%20alley%20where%20one%20is%20forced%20to%20a%20debate%20a%20counterfactual%20scenario%20and%20rely%20on%20internal%20US%20military%20sources%20that%20are%20not%20neutral.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20simpler%20question%20can%20be%20used%20to%20form%20an%20ethical%20judgment%3A%20%E2%80%9CDid%20the%20Truman%20administration%20do%20everything%20possible%20to%20save%20lives%20and%20seek%20less%20violent%20alternatives%20to%20the%20atomic%20bomb%3F%E2%80%9D%20Even%20the%20limited%20discussion%20presented%20above%2C%20which%20forms%20a%20small%20part%20of%20the%20voluminous%20historical%20record%2C%20shows%20that%20the%20answer%20is%20negative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20different%20perspective%20is%20provided%20by%20Szilard%E2%80%99s%20recollection%20of%20his%20meeting%20with%20James%20Byrnes%2C%20who%20was%20Truman%E2%80%99s%20secretary%20of%20state%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20bombings.%20When%20Szilard%20tried%20to%20caution%20Byrnes%20against%20using%20the%20bomb%2C%20Byrnes%20explained%20that%20%E2%80%9CRussia%20might%20be%20more%20manageable%20if%20impressed%20by%20American%20military%20might%2C%20and%20that%20a%20demonstration%20of%20the%20bomb%20might%20impress%20Russia%E2%80%9D.%20This%20implies%20that%20the%20bomb%20was%20used%20by%20the%20United%20States%2C%20not%20out%20of%20necessity%2C%20but%20to%20establish%20its%20geopolitical%20dominance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20examination%20of%20postwar%20US%20policy%20bolsters%20this%20view%2C%20since%20it%20shows%20how%20readily%20the%20US%20government%20is%20prepared%20to%20use%20violence%20and%20terror%20in%20pursuit%20of%20its%20strategic%20objectives.%20When%20the%20United%20States%20attacked%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20it%20dropped%20millions%20of%20tons%20of%20bombs%20and%20this%20intervention%20led%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC2440905%2F%5C%22%3Emillions%20of%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%20began%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9Cshock-and-awe%E2%80%9D%20campaign%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dodccrp.org%2Ffiles%2FUllman_Shock.pdf%5C%22%3Eexplicitly%20sought%20to%20achieve%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnon-nuclear%20equivalent%20of%20the%20impact%20that%20the%20atomic%20weapons%20dropped%20on%20Hiroshima%20and%20Nagasaki%20had%20on%20the%20Japanese%E2%80%9D.%20This%20invasion%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosmedicine%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pmed.1001533%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20deaths%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Iraq.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHollywood%20is%20well%20known%20for%20glorifying%20US%20wars.%20%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20directed%20more%20skilfully%20than%20most%20movies%2C%20and%20its%20message%20is%20more%20subtle.%20But%2C%20ultimately%2C%20its%20effect%20is%20to%20place%20a%20glossy%20veneer%20on%20the%20ugly%20reality%20of%20the%20US%20imperial%20project%20and%20the%20complicity%20of%20those%20who%20contribute%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESuvrat%20Raju%20is%20a%20theoretical%20physicist%20with%20the%20International%20Centre%20for%20Theoretical%20Sciences%20(Bengaluru).%20The%20views%20expressed%20are%20personal%20and%20do%20not%20reflect%20those%20of%20his%20institution.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20article%20provides%20links%20to%20and%20details%20of%20online%20and%20offline%20resources%2C%20wherever%20possible%2C%20and%20the%20author%20encourages%20readers%20to%20follow%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691302412000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F06114151%2FOppenheimer-Movie-Poster_1658466334143_1658466388193_1658466388193.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Foppenheimer-did-not-stop-at-building-a-nuclear-bomb-he-also-pushed-for-its-use-in-japan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Christopher%20Nolan's%20movie%20is%20skilfully%20made%2C%20but%20its%20effect%20is%20to%20place%20a%20glossy%20veneer%20on%20the%20ugly%20reality%20of%20the%20US%20imperial%20project%20and%20the%20complicity%20of%20those%20who%20contribute%20to%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A115%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Foppenheimer-did-not-stop-at-building-a-nuclear-bomb-he-also-pushed-for-its-use-in-japan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Video%3A%20Raj%20Kundra%20spots%20a%20bizarre%20mask%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691302312000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102467172%2Cimgsize-113022.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fraj-kundra-grabs-attention-once-again-with-bizarre-mask-as-he-gets-spotted-with-wife-shilpa-shetty-see-pics%2Farticleshow%2F102467172.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102467172.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fraj-kundra-grabs-attention-once-again-with-bizarre-mask-as-he-gets-spotted-with-wife-shilpa-shetty-see-pics%2Farticleshow%2F102467172.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20least%2030%20people%20killed%20and%2060%20injured%20after%20train%20derails%20in%20Pakistan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691302140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%